as much as I say, namely, that the reason wherefore the converted Iewes were so apt to be scandalized by such as cared not for the Ceremoniall Law, and held themselves obliged to observe the same, was, because they saw not how they could be exeemed from the ordinances and statutes of the Law of Moses with which they had been educated and accustomed.
